channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: The Devil Went Down to Georgia - and Is Puttin' a Whuppin' on Joe Biden
DeSantis signs law banning 'intentional' release of balloons
item.description: Florida has now banned the intentional release of balloons within the state, a move backed by ocean conservationists, cattle farmers and other groups.

item.title: US Ambassador: China Undermining Democracy
item.description: Nicholas Burns, the American ambassador to China, is accusing the country of undermining democracy, according to The Wall Street Journal. Burns told the Journal China is intimidating citizens who attend U.S.-organized events in China, restricting the embassy's social media...

item.title: Big Win for Missouri and Six Other States on Biden's Latest Student Loan Scheme
Hunter Biden's law license suspended following historic guilty verdict
item.description: First son Hunter Biden's law license was suspended in Washington, D.C., following the guilty verdict in his historic gun trial in Wilmington, Delaware.

item.title: Nobel Economists: Biden Agenda 'Superior' to Trump's
item.description: With little over four months to go before the presidential election, 16 Nobel prize-winning economists are cautioning voters on what they see as the inflationary pitfalls of another Trump administration. Echoing President Joe Biden's reelection campaign, the group of Nobel...

item.title: More Horror in Jocelyn Nonragay Murder Case: Sexual Assault 'Likely'
'It's just obscene': House eyes crackdown on US dollars going to Taliban
item.description: Rep. Tim Burchett told Fox News Digital that he hopes his bill will dry up funding to the Taliban, which has ruled Afghanistan since August 2021.

item.title: Ben Carson to Newsmax: Biden Camp Won't Agree to Drug Test
item.description: Dr. Ben Carson told Newsmax on Tuesday that Joe Biden's presidential campaign won't agree to a drug test ahead of Thursday's debate even though it would be "helpful to allay" concerns that Americans have about the sitting president.

item.title: Justice Thomas’ Ally Believes There Were ‘Errors and Deceptions’ in Reports of Gifts the Justice Received
Trump offers to take drug screening if Biden agrees to same test
item.description: Former President Trump urged President Biden via Truth Social to take a drug test before this week's presidential, saying he would be willing to do the same.

item.title: Analysis: No Fortune 100 CEOs Have Donated to Trump Bid
item.description: According to a recent analysis of campaign contributions, not a single Fortune 100 CEO has donated to the campaign for former President Donald Trump thus far, a New York Times op-ed noted on Sunday.

item.title: Woman Who Will Always Be Remembered for Losing to Donald Trump Has Advice for Joe Biden
Julian Assange spotted boarding plane to remote US territory amid plea deal
item.description: Julian Assange spent $500,000 on a flight from London to a remote U.S. territory to avoid setting foot on the U.S. mainland on Tuesday.

item.title: Karoline Leavitt to Newsmax: Getting Booted From CNN Proves Point
item.description: Trump 2024 press secretary Karoline Leavitt, a day after having her interview stopped on CNN for saying network anchors Jake Tapper and Dana Bash, who will be moderating Thursday's presidential debate, are biased against former President Donald Trump, told Newsmax Tuesday...
